    "body": "Thanks for trying the experimental fix @dankrad. Out of interest, what SSD does this machine have, and are there a lot of other processes writing to disk? Rough numbers from `iotop` would be useful. My current theory about the compaction is that on slow disks it causes a lot of writes to be buffered in memory, which gets worse and worse as more compactions run and the disk can’t keep up (we _were_ running every finalization)",
